f=Executive Office/marcus/custom/decision-critic/SKILL.md · in=decision-critic structured adversarial-review skill. takes decision, plan, strategy person about commit to, stress-tests before commitment rather after failure. built merging two marketplace sources independently converged technique family (Steelman Attack Pre-Mortem) combining their distinct strengths: `strategy-red-team`'s load-bearing-assumption ranking kill-criteria output, `red-team`'s WWHTBT ("What True") framing validating proposals. · p=Give operator (marcus, whoever marcus advising) sharper decision longer risk list. skill exists catch failure mode plan survives because received polite feedback, because it's actually sound. triggered before big, hard-to-reverse calls: resource allocation between ventures, new strategic direction, major partnership spend commitment, any proposal about front board. · wu=Triggers: "big decision," "stress test this," "is plan solid," "pressure-test strategy," "before commit X," any time marcus about finalize recommendation high-impact irreversible consequences. skill mechanism run *before* decision crosses escalation threshold, after. for: routine, low-stakes, easily-reversible decisions. Running full adversarial review trivial calls wastes operator's attention trains them ignore output. · st:/ Protocol=`Extract load-bearing claims \· -> Steelman each claim, then attack the steelman \· -> Reframe surviving attacks as WWHTBT conditions \· -> Rank by impact x likelihood x cheapness-to-test \· -> Report: kill-assumptions, what's sound, what's unassessable` · st:/ Protocol=skill runs five phases: · h3:Phase Extract Claims=Read plan/decision full. List everything asserts true about user, market, constraint, mechanism, timeline, resourcing. Separate **load-bearing** claims (if false, plan dies) cosmetic ones. load-bearing claims proceed Phase plan vague incomplete, ask one clarifying question before proceeding rather guessing what's load-bearing. · h3:Phase Steelman, Attack=core discipline borrowed source skills, non-negotiable: load-bearing claim, first state **strongest, charitable version** true (the steelman). attack *that* version weaker strawman. attack strawman worthless correctly ignored operator. Write surviving failure mode **"Fails ___"** concrete falsifiable. "Fails activation isn't actually constraint" beats "execution risk." · h3:Phase WWHTBT Reframe="Fails ___" statement, restate "What True" condition: what true about world claim hold? reframing (from `red-team`) makes assumption testable rather criticized turns "this work" "here specific thing check." · h3:Phase 4 — Rank=Rank surviving kill-assumptions **(impact wrong) (likelihood wrong) (cheapness test)**. top list what test *this week* high-impact, plausibly wrong, cheap check. Surface ranking explicitly; don't bury under wall text. top-ranked kill-assumption, produce: · h3:Phase 4 — Rank=**Claim:** the load-bearing assertion., **Fails if:** precise, falsifiable condition breaks plan., **WWHTBT:** what true claim hold., **Evidence get week:** specific data, query, conversation confirm kill cheaply., **Kill criterion:** threshold which operator stop change course., **Cheapest test:** smallest experiment moves belief. · h3:Phase 5 — Report=`## Decision Critic: [decision/plan in one line] \·  \· ### Top Kill-Assumptions (ranked) \· [3-5 max, using the Phase 4 template] \· ` · pr=**No strawmanning.** Attack steelman don't attack all., **No generic risk lists.** item specific *this* decision "market risk" acceptable output., **No fabrication.** claim genuinely well-reasoned, say plainly. critic manufactures doubt seem thorough useless one rubber-stamps everything., **Proportional response.** Minor, unlikely failure modes don't justify major rework. Five real kill-assumptions tests beat twenty generic risks., **Rank ruthlessly.** cheapest high-impact test entire point exercise don't let get lost list., **End what do, what fear.** emotional job skill relief fear confidently shipping wrong bet. · f=plan/decision underspecified extract load-bearing claims, stop ask operator fill gap rather inventing claims attack., independent second model reachable cross-checking, run single-model default degraded mode, note wasn't cross-checked., operator wants second opinion another model reachable, optionally run plan through flag disagreements different model families miss different things. add step unless asked., load-bearing claim survives attack, say directly "What's Well-Reasoned" rather forcing manufactured risks ranked list. · b:with Other marcus Skills=`decision-critic` stress-tests decision already framed. generate decision itself that's upstream work (e.g. okr-cascade objective-setting, venture-priority-matrix resource-allocation scoring)., `decision-critic` replace board escalation high-stakes spend; pre-escalation quality gate, substitute governance sign-off.